title: For Sale:  CZ 40B
location: West Lebanon, New Hampshire, United States
postcontent: I have for sale is a rare CZ 40B pistol. These guns were built by CZ for just a couple of years and difficult to find today. In 1998, Colt partnered with CZ to have them design a good double action pistol. The result was the Colt Z40 and, as the name suggested, it was developed for and chambered only in 40S&W. It shares the 1911's grip angle, which was a design stipulation that Colt implemented. To make a long story short, CZ produced the Z40 for Colt for about a year before the business relationship soured and Colt dropped it from their lineup. CZ continued to produce the pistol for another year or so under the moniker "40B". With such a short production run for this pistol under both names, there aren't many around. The only finish it was offered in is the black finish that CZ uses for its other handguns. The 1911-style grips are black rubber. The 40B is different from anything Colt or CZ produced before or since. However, like everything CZ produces, its a very well built pistol. Unlike most of the metal CZ 75 based pistols, this has an aluminum frame, not steel. Despite the fact that this pistol looks so different from the CZ 75, the action and trigger have an identical feel. When you handle it, you know you have a CZ in your hands. Like other CZ pistols, the slide rides inside the frame, like a Sig P210. The ergonomics are outstanding and the CZ 40B is very comfortable in hand. This was also the pistol that CZ later based the smaller RAMI off of, as you may be able to tell from its appearance. I shot the gun less than 50 rounds and I don't think it was shot much prior to that. The 40B features a smooth double action trigger pull and a clean SA trigger pull. In typical CZ fashion, accuracy is very good and quality is high. It comes with one Clinton-era 10 round 40S&W mag, but I see magazines available for these pistols often. The barrel length is 4.25". The sights are the 3 white dot type and work great. The front strap features vertical serrations for a secure grip. Disassembly works just like a CZ 75B, as does the safety. You must be a NH resident with LTC and be over 21. Price is $450.00.
